This paper is primarily focused on visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves the use of a Siamese network and attentional mechanism, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed approach, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
